	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I will answer as it seems you bought the original cart.
<br />The EPROMs are identical to any other Nintendo game, that is the modification should in theory be the same as for a TLROM board.
<br />
<br />The only difference is that with the MMC5 there is room for 1024k PRG and CHR chips, that no game ever used as far I know. It's just a matter of normally unused pins that would be used for A19, that you don't use anyway  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=":wink:" title="Wink" />

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


